<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Malbak gets unbundling green light.</title>
<headline>Malbak gets unbundling green light.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-03-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shareholders in South African holding firm Malbak Ltd gave the green light to the group's unbundling on Monday by voting for the approval of the scheme.</p>
<p>The plan still requires the approval of the High Court, which will probably give its ruling towards the end of April, the firm said in a statement.</p>
<p>Malbak is disposing of its unlisted investments and plans to distribute the sale proceeds to its shareholders in cash at the same time as distributing shares in its listed subsidiaries.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
